{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_1lichtenstein_ver02/data/sn83045462/00280601664/1937122301/0741.xml":{"full_text":"CURB LIST GOES\nTO LOW LEVELS\nLeaders Decline Fractions\nto Around 3 Points in\nMild Selling.\nBy th* AitocUled Press,\nVEW YORK, Dec. 23\u2014Leading\ncurb chares were knor ked down frac- I\ntions to around 3 points by moderate\ntelling today.\nShowing some resistance, Lake Shore\nMines, Cord Corp. and Pan-American\nAirways crawled ahead fractionally.\nIn late trading Sherwin-Williams\nwas down 3, Newmont lost 2 and Bra\nliiian Traction and Aluminum Co.\ngave up I each.\n\nFire Insurance\nVolumes to Show\nModerate Gains\nP> the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK Dec. 23\u2014Despite\nsomewhat lower rates, fire insurance\ncompanies generally are expected to\nreport, moderate gains in premium vol\numes for 1937. a survey by Standard\nStatistics Co., made public today, said.\nAutomobile insurance has accounted\nfor much of the gains, although other\nlines have also improved. Fire losses\nwere 4 per cent, lower for the first 10\nmonths, resulting in higher net- un\nderwriting profits.\nThe survey expresses the opinion\nthat with unfavorable business condi- j\ntions in prospect for the first half of\n1938 losses may well increase and\nvolume of premiums decline.\ni 1 i\nCURB BONDS\nDOMESTIC BONDS.\nHigh. Low. Noon.\nAla Power 4'is '67 82 82 82\nAla Power 5s '46 A _ 101', Ini', 101',\nAm G A E 5s 2028 107s, 107'a 107'a\nAppalach E P 5s '56 105', 105', 105',\nArk P A L 5s '56 !i:i'a 93'i 9.3'a\nAs El Ind 4'as '53 36', 36 36\nAs G A E 4'as '49 C 28',, 78', 28',\u00ab\nAs G A E 5s RS 31 30\u2019, 31\nAs G A E 5'aS'38 i c reg 59'a 59'a 59'a\nAs T A T 5'as '55 A 71\u2019, 711, 7 1s,\nAtl Gas Lt 4'as '55 9.3 93 93\nBald Lo 6s '50 72V, 70 70'*\nBirm El 4'as '68 82 82 82\nBtrming Gas 5s 59 58 57'2 57*i\nCan Pac tis 42 HIT\u2019, 1074* 1074*\nCent I1PS 5s '56 E 100', loo\u2019, 100',\nCen I1PS 41 as '67 F 97\u2019, 9'!\u2019- P7'a\nCent St E! 5s '48 40 40 40\nCent St El 5\u2