deral Reserve member\nbanks advanced during the period\nended December 15.\nBankers noted the turn came at a\ntime when stock and bond prices were\nimproving slightly, whereas the pre\nvious slump coincided with the fall\nbreak in security prices.\nInterbank deposits of foreign banks\nwith Reserve members in 101 cities,\nreported by the Reserve Board, com\npared as follows:\nWeek ended December 15 *415,000.000\nPrevious week _ 4oa.ooo.oo0\nSame period last year_... 450.000.000\nCHRISTMAS TRADE LAOS.\nCUMBERLAND, Md\u201e Dec. 23 (i<P).\u2014\nHarold W. Smith, secretary of the\nChamber of Commerce, said Christmas\nbuying here is 20 per cent below the\nmark set last year. He blamed the\nemployment decrease here. There is a\ntendency, he said, for buyers to pur\nchase cheaper articles.\nINSURANCE STOCKS\nNEW YORK. Dec. 23 1J8.\u2014New 'York\nsecurity Dealers\u2019 Association\nBid. Asked.\nAetna Cas (3e* 84 88\nAetna Ins (1.60)_ .39% 41%\nAetna Life (la* __ _ 22% ->4%\nAm Equit (1.6<*al. _ 25 26%\nAm Ins Nwk (%a)_ 9*4 11%\nAm Reins il.20g)_ _ 31%\nAm Reserve (la>__ 20*4 \u201dl>.\nAm Surety (2%)- 37 39\nAutomobile (la* _ _ 24 25%\nBalt Amer (,20a)_ 5\nCarolina *1.30* _ 18% 19*4\nCity of N Y *1.20* _ 17% 19\nConn Oen Lif (.80) _ 22 \u2018>4\nCon tin Cas (1.20) \"4 \u25a018*\u00ab\nfid A Dep (4aI __ _ 95 99%\nFirem s Nwk (.30)_ _ 7% 9\nFrank Fire (la* _ _ 04% \u00b06\nGen Reinsur (2*__I-\" 28% 3(1%\nGlen Falls (1.80* 35% 371,\nGlobe Rep (,8(tal. 12 13%\nGlobe A- Rut _ 27'a 32\nGreat Amer (la)_ 19% 21*4\nHanover (1.60) __ _ 25 26%\nHartford Fire (2)_ Bn*. 62%\nHome Fire Bee _ 1% 2%\nHome Ins 11 a) _ __ 25% 27%\nHomestead (1> _ 14 15%\nKnickerbocker (.80)_ 10 11%\nLincoln Fire 2% 3%\nMaryland Cas _ 3', 4%\nMass Bond (.3\u2018at 3\u00ab% 39%\nMerc Ins Pr (.31*) _ 4 6\nNatl fit' <2) 60% 62%\nNatl Liberty (,20a) 6% ,7%\nNew Hampshire (1.60a)_ 4(1 4l%\nN Y Fire (,80a*- 14 15%\nNor River (1), _ 24% 26%\nPhoenix (2a* __ 7.3 75\nProv Wash (la) _ 24*4 26%\n,'P' In (1-30>_ 19% 20%